    <!-- Add insight / key takeaway directly related to activity / learner experience -->

    <insight>
        <p>
            Hire purchase is a method of buying goods where a buyer pays a deposit and the remaining amount in instalments while using the item.
        </p>

        <p>
            Although it makes expensive goods more affordable in the short term, the total amount paid is usually higher than the cash price due to added costs spread over time.
        </p>

        <p>
            Let:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> P = \amp \;\text{Cash price} </mrow>
                <mrow> D = \amp \; \text{Deposit} </mrow>
                <mrow> x =  \amp \;\text{Instalment amount} </mrow>
                <mrow> n = \amp \; \text{Number of instalments} </mrow>
                <mrow> H = \amp \;\text{Hire purchase price} </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>

        <p>
            Then:
        </p>

        <p>
            <md>
                <mrow> H = \amp \;D + xn </mrow>
                <mrow> I = \amp \;H - P </mrow>
                <mrow> R = \amp \;\frac{H - P}{P} \times 100\% </mrow>
            </md>
        </p>

        <p>
            The key idea is that hire purchase increases accessibility to goods, but it also increases the total cost of ownership. Therefore, careful financial decision-making is necessary before choosing this method of payment.
        </p>
    </insight>

    <!-- Add further instruction (not in a block) to develop ideas as needed -->

